        "title": "What are the SCons alternatives?",
        "body": "<p>I have projects in C++, Java and Python. Projects in C++ export SWIG interfaces so they can be used by Java and Python projects.<\/p>\n\n<p>My question is: what building mechanism can I use to manage dependencies and build these projects?<\/p>\n\n<p>I have used SCons and GYP. They are fairly easy to use and allow plugins (code-generators, compilers, packers). I'd like to know whether there are alternatives, in particular with native support for C++, Java and Python.<\/p>\n\n<p>I develop in Linux platform, but I'd like to be able to build in mac and win platforms as well.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 4141511,
